\section{Qualitative Case Analyses: Telugu}
\label{sec:qualitative_appendix}

We present two detailed case analyses for Telugu, one covering
zero-shot and few-shot conditions and one covering the translation
condition. These cases are representative of the error patterns
described in the Clinical Error Taxonomy (Section~6). Telugu was
selected as the primary case language because it exhibits the widest
range of error types across conditions and the largest absolute
performance gap between zero-shot and SFT.

\subsection*{Case A: Zero-Shot vs.\ Few-Shot (scenario\_52)}

\noindent\textbf{Clinical context.}
A follow-up consultation focused on throat symptoms (four weeks of
discomfort, voice change), behavioral risk factors (Pane Makh
2--3\,/\,day, alcohol 3--4\,/\,week, rare cigarettes), evaluation
planning (fiber-optic laryngoscopy if needed, followed by biopsy or
imaging), MDT coordination, and a structured three-year follow-up cadence.

