\noindent\textbf{Key observation.}
Unlike the zero-shot and few-shot cases, most errors in the translation
output are traceable to specific IndicTrans2 translation failures
rather than to the summarizer. The tobacco use phrase was semantically
collapsed to ``reduce their space,'' eliminating a key behavioral
risk factor entirely. The age-based HPV eligibility criterion was
rendered such that the numeral 45 survived translation but its
governing unit (``years'') was lost, and the summarizer filled the
gap by hallucinating a per-person or per-month quota. The
speaker-role markers encoded in Telugu verb morphology were
neutralized in the English rendering, causing clinician advice to
be attributed to the patient. These are not errors the summarizer
can recover from; they reflect fundamental limitations of the current
IndicTrans2 translation quality for Telugu clinical text.
